cicognara-rails.title: Troubleshooting Harvard count from resource portal dump

comments.body:
We found that the Getty data dump includes indeed 83 files for Harvard, all of them are found on `resourcedump_2022-10-31-part3.zip` (download from here http://portal.getty.edu/resources/json_data/resourcedump.xml)

During processing 18 of them are failing to import with message "no matching Book entry for DCL xxx".

```
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990016390930203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:8w6/vol01
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990054802000203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:nw6
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990085529710203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:jcv
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990023458840203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:0m3
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990056313670203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:6st
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990065165000203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:9ks
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990096206550203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:jwk
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990052901710203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:p0k
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990049089240203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:vs9
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990054838920203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:ckv
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990021547270203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:p35
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990034493580203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:6cq/vol01
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990056860020203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:cd4
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990018263160203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:c6c
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990000060160203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:111
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990061254250203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:4x6
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990028582360203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:m8v
Unable to import http://portal.getty.edu/books/hul_990003403540203941 - no matching Book entry for DCL dcl:scb/vol01
```

It seems that these records are not found on the source `catalogo.tei.xml` coming from https://github.com/pulibrary/cicognara-catalogo/

The root of the problem seems to be that the records are failed to be imported because there is no match for them in the `Books` table. 

It seems that the `Books` table is populated with data from the `public/cicognara.mrx.xml` (or is it `public/cicognara.marc.xml`?) and there is indeed no match for the missing records in this MARC XML file. 

This is the code that process the MARC XML: https://github.com/pulibrary/cicognara-rails/blob/main/lib/cicognara/tei_indexer.rb#L88 -- it is possible that the `Books` table was populated with the [BookIndexer](https://github.com/pulibrary/cicognara-rails/blob/main/lib/cicognara/book_indexer.rb) but it is not clear to me how to trigger this code.

Notice that just adding the problematic DCL numbers to the `catalogo.tei.xml` file as indicated [here](https://github.com/pulibrary/cicognara-catalogo/#assigning-new-dcl-numbers) does not seem to fix the issue since the match is not found on the Books table.

Here is a snippet of the `public/cicognara.mrx.xml` that shows how the DCL number and CICO are recorded for MARC records under field `024`:

```
...
  <record>
    <leader>01296cam a2200289Mi 4500</leader>
    <controlfield tag="001">10084756</controlfield>
    <controlfield tag="005">20170116133726.0</controlfield>
    <controlfield tag="007">hu uuu---uuuu</controlfield>
    <controlfield tag="008">000202s1708    xx      b     000 0 ger d</controlfield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="035">
      <subfield code="a">(OCoLC)ocn313540341</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1="7" ind2=" " tag="024">
      <subfield code="a">465</subfield>
      <subfield code="2">cico</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1="7" ind2=" " tag="024">
      <subfield code="a">dcl:zc5</subfield>
      <subfield code="2">dclib</subfield>
    </datafield>
...
```

Sort of good news. I hard-coded a fake MARC record in `cicognara.mrx.xml` with the proper subfields to represent one of the missing records (`dcl:nw6`) 
```
    <datafield ind1="7" ind2=" " tag="024">
      <subfield code="a">365</subfield>
      <subfield code="2">cico</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1="7" ind2=" " tag="024">
      <subfield code="a">dcl:nw6</subfield>
      <subfield code="2">dclib</subfield>
    </datafield>
```
re-ran the import and the record was imported (see screenshot below):

![cicognara_nw6](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/568286/204646288-a3089628-924d-464a-aec8-a5273093bdad.png)

Surprisingly some of the data shows correctly, like the author, date, and title *even though* my fake hard coded MARC record had other values. It's possible the site iss picking these values from the `catalogo.tei.xml` since I added the attribute `corresp="dcl:nw6"` to the record on that file.

site looks good. tried a reindex and got https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/51733/faults/90930647

update: that's an existing issue in prod: https://github.com/pulibrary/dpul/issues/1300

lae-blacklight.title: Genre/Format is no longer displaying in LAE site for items

comments.body:
**Same item used for all examples in LAE, DPUL and Figgy:**

Example of current display on LAE site (no genre/format field is displaying here):
![Screen Shot 2022-11-29 at 3 44 26 PM (2)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45043014/204645307-4e2b4b64-5543-42d4-94a3-da66df03c3fb.png)

Example of current display on unpublished DPUL LAE site (format: Posters is showing)
![Screen Shot 2022-11-29 at 3 45 52 PM (2)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45043014/204645479-a379a9ed-cee5-45f9-a51a-6d743dd69026.png)

Example of current display in scanned resource within figgy (genre: Posters is showing)
![Screen Shot 2022-11-29 at 3 52 27 PM (2)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45043014/204645596-a5b30dd2-406c-4634-81e5-b373bac48ce4.png)

### Sudden Priority Justification
LAE is in maintenance only status, however I am marking this as sudden priority because it is not a request for a new feature or enhancement. Rather, it is to fix something that was showing as part of the metadata in the past on the LAE site an now is not.  Continued display of format/genre of an ephemeral item within a format-diverse collection is important to researchers working with this content.
